We solve the quadratic equation \(x^2 - 11x - 42 = 0\) using the quadratic formula:
\[
x = \frac{11 \pm \sqrt{(-11)^2 - 4(1)(-42)}}{2}
   = \frac{11 \pm \sqrt{121 + 168}}{2}
   = \frac{11 \pm \sqrt{289}}{2}
   = \frac{11 \pm 17}{2}.
\]
Thus the two distinct solutions are \(x = \frac{11+17}{2}=14\) and \(x = \frac{11-17}{2}=-3\). The larger of these is \(14\).
