reasoning_trace:
To compute \(\binom{7}{4}\), use the formula \(\binom{n}{k} = \frac{n!}{k!(n-k)!}\).  
Here \(n = 7\) and \(k = 4\), so  

\[
\binom{7}{4} = \frac{7!}{4! \cdot 3!}
= \frac{7 \times 6 \times 5 \times 4!}{4! \times (3 \times 2 \times 1)}
= \frac{7 \times 6 \times 5}{3 \times 2 \times 1}
= \frac{210}{6}
= 35.
\]  
Thus the value is 35.</think> <answer>35</answer>

